  <prompt>
    Create IFileIndexingService interface that defines the unified RAG indexing pipeline.
    The interface should expose three entry points (OBO, App-only download, Pre-extracted content)
    that all converge to the same underlying pipeline. Include supporting types and result models.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in interface design and the RAG indexing architecture.
    Follow ADR-013 for AI architecture and ADR-007 for file access patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    IFileIndexingService interface created with three entry point methods.
    Supporting types (FileIndexingOptions, FileIndexingResult) defined.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      This interface defines the unified entry point for RAG indexing. Three methods support
      different authentication/content scenarios, but all converge to the same pipeline:
      text extraction → chunking → embedding → indexing. See design.md architecture diagram.
    </background>
